  Prey tells the story of Tommy, a Cherokee garage mechanic stuck on a 
  reservation going nowhere. His life changes when an otherworldly crisis 
  forces him to awaken spiritual powers from his long-forgotten birthright. 
  Abducted along with his people to a menacing mothership orbiting Earth, he 
  sets out to save himself and his girlfriend and eventually his planet. Prey
  is serious, dark story, based on authentic Cherokee mythology. Themes of 
  sacrifice, love and responsibility are explored and the story dives into 
  emotional territory not yet explored by similar games.
